Without having held the aedileship (ξ 37), Murena obtained in 65 BC the praetorship, again with Sulpicius sor a colleague3 but had been more fortunate than the latter in the duties given him by the lot: for while he had got the iuris dictio urbana, the irksorne task of conducting the enquiries de pay-lgm had fallen to Sul- picius (§§ 35—42).
